config BR2_PACKAGE_ZENOH
	bool "zenoh"
	depends on BR2_PACKAGE_HOST_RUSTC
	help
	  Zenoh is a pub/sub/query protocol unifying data in motion,
	  data at rest and computations. It is designed for robotics,
	  IoT, and edge computing.

	  Zenoh is the recommended ROS2 middleware for ROS 2 Kilted
	  and later, replacing DDS in many use cases.

	  Features:
	  - Ultra-low latency pub/sub (<10us)
	  - Works over any network (LAN, WAN, WiFi, 5G)
	  - Minimal footprint for embedded systems
	  - Native ROS2 rmw_zenoh support
	  - Automatic peer discovery

	  https://zenoh.io/

comment "zenoh requires host Rust toolchain"
	depends on !BR2_PACKAGE_HOST_RUSTC
